message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The vaccine containing a noninfectious glycoprotein is likely the hepatitis B vaccine, which will help prevent infection by the hepatitis B virus. The other options are not prevented by the hepatitis B vaccine.

We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. Among the options, only Hepatitis D virus has a vaccine that contains a noninfectious glycoprotein. Poliovirus vaccine is an inactivated virus, Bordetella pertussis vaccine contains inactivated bacterial toxins, and rotavirus vaccine contains live attenuated viruses.

Poliovirus has a live attenuated vaccine, Bordetella pertussis and Rotavirus have killed or live attenuated whole cell vaccines.
